Notes.Text:
This update for texlive fixes the following issues:

- CVE-2023-32700: Fixed arbitrary code execution in LuaTeX (bsc#1211389).
Notes.Title: Details

Vulnerabilities.Description: LuaTeX before 1.17.0 allows execution of arbitrary shell commands when compiling a TeX file obtained from an untrusted source. This occurs because luatex-core.lua lets the original io.popen be accessed. This also affects TeX Live before 2023 r66984 and MiKTeX before 23.5.
